19:46.512 --> 19:50.357
If the only time we're willing to obey us, we're being threatened, that's not real obedience.

19:51.839 --> 19:56.466
In the case of Israel, this failure to trust becomes really the final straw.

19:57.410 --> 20:01.637
God had made a promise to give them this homeland all the way back to their ancestor Abraham.

20:02.939 --> 20:07.247
And these people have seen him perform miracle after miracle after miracle.

20:08.709 --> 20:14.198
He has brought them to this point to Kedish Barnia by caring for them time after time.

20:14.459 --> 20:18.986
When time after time, they've expressed the same kind of attitude, this lack of trust.

20:19.988 --> 20:20.709
There's no water.

20:21.210 --> 20:22.072
We're all going to die a thirst.

20:22.112 --> 20:23.474
Why'd you bring us out here to die?

20:23.906 --> 20:27.491
We're trapped by the Red Sea, the Egyptians are gonna kill us, why'd you bring us out here to die?

20:27.851 --> 20:35.601
Everything they come up against, their first response is, God must be against us, he brought us here to die, and God has continuously, in grace, provided for them.

20:36.582 --> 20:45.934
And yet here, once again, despite all of that history, they come to Kedish Barnia, they see something that looks too big for them to handle, and their response is, let's kill Moses and go the other way.

20:45.954 --> 20:52.082
And Lord says, no, you're not gonna enter.

20:53.506 --> 20:55.469
This is going to be reserved for a new generation.

20:57.292 --> 21:08.290
And the result is that instead of a victory campaign, that entire generation except for Joshua and Caleb were sent on a literal dead end 40 year journey in the wilderness.

21:10.053 --> 21:20.850
And only when the last one had died where they brought back to this same place and brought back to boldly go and conquer where their parents had only grumbled and doubted.

21:22.978 --> 21:32.590
As I was studying this passage, again, it was Tim Keller who helped me to make a fresh connection between this story and the gospel.

21:34.212 --> 21:44.705
The connection begins with the recognition that Moses was writing this Deuteronomy account 40 years after those fateful events at Kadesh Barnea.

21:46.167 --> 21:48.410
We miss the time span sometimes, reading our Bibles.

21:49.211 --> 21:51.634
You flip your page and you just jump 40 years.

21:51.746 --> 21:56.252
or 400 years, or the case may be, we forget the time that's elapsed, all that's gone on.

21:56.312 --> 22:03.140
But 40 years of elapsed, that old generation has died out as Moses is writing these words of Deuteronomy.

22:03.681 --> 22:05.603
He's writing to the children of that generation.

22:07.385 --> 22:16.156
In other words, the fact that this message was being written was evidence that God had still been faithful to his people, even though they had not been faithful to him.

22:17.978 --> 22:21.042
And the question that Keller asked was, why?

22:22.722 --> 22:27.569
The answer, you can trace all the way back to this in Deuteronomy chapter one.

22:28.610 --> 22:34.037
Not one of these men's as evil generations will see the good land that I swore to give to your fathers.

22:35.219 --> 22:35.940
There's the key.

22:36.921 --> 22:40.867
There was a promise God had made to their fathers that God was going to keep.

22:41.668 --> 22:48.897
And that commitment finds his origin all the way back with Abraham, the great, great, great, great, great, great granddaddy of the Hebrew people.

22:49.638 --> 22:52.242
And you find that all the way back in Genesis 15, 18.

22:52.546 --> 22:55.951
On that day, the Lord made a covenant with Abraham.

22:57.053 --> 23:02.641
And the covenant involved that I'm going to give you, I'm gonna make them a great nation, I'm gonna give them a great land.

23:03.763 --> 23:10.033
And the covenant was ratified in a way that at first glance seems pretty weird to modern sensibilities.

23:10.053 --> 23:16.763
If you go back and read this story and you don't understand the context, you're gonna say, that's probably the strangest ritual I have ever seen.

23:17.905 --> 23:21.330
Abraham was told that he should cut several animals in half

23:21.762 --> 23:25.088
and lay the halves on the ground opposite each other.

23:25.929 --> 23:29.936
So you've got a half here, half there, half here, half there laid out on the ground.

23:30.537 --> 23:35.225
And then something was going to happen with that.

23:35.265 --> 23:38.130
Now Abraham probably understood right away what this was all about.

23:38.911 --> 23:45.522
In ancient times, if a ruling king wanted to establish an irrevocable agreement with one of his subjects,

23:46.082 --> 23:57.414
They would establish the rules, the agreement, and then they'd go through this ritual of dividing animals in half, and the king's subjects would then pass down this aisle in between halves.

23:58.676 --> 24:02.440
Never the king, just the king's subjects.

24:02.460 --> 24:11.630
And what the subjects are saying through this ritual is just saying, if we don't keep our end of the bargain, may what happened to these animals happen to us.

24:12.751 --> 24:15.154
It's kind of a blood oath, if you will.

24:15.650 --> 24:20.037
And so as Abraham begins to lay out these animal parts, he knows what's coming.

24:20.898 --> 24:24.664
God has just said, I have sworn something, we are ending into a covenant here.

24:25.044 --> 24:30.112
We're gonna go through the usual legal process to validate that covenant.

24:31.995 --> 24:34.338
But then here's the unexpected part of Abraham's covenant.

24:36.081 --> 24:39.647
Abraham was never asked to pass between the pieces.

24:41.509 --> 24:42.631
That's what should have happened next.

24:42.651 --> 24:44.594
Lord Jesus had lame out, okay Abraham,

24:44.802 --> 24:48.487
Walk the aisle, promise me that you're going to keep your end of the deal.

24:49.669 --> 24:50.931
Abraham is never asked to do that.

24:51.011 --> 25:00.484
Instead, what's recorded is a mysterious fiery torch, kind of like that fiery cloud that was leading Israel in the wilderness.

25:01.265 --> 25:02.968
It passed between the pieces.

25:04.189 --> 25:06.733
In other words, a symbol of God himself.

25:08.175 --> 25:10.438
Who was it that ratified the covenant?

25:11.820 --> 25:13.042
It was God himself.

25:14.370 --> 25:16.733
He never asked Abraham to do it.

25:16.854 --> 25:18.296
It was God who ratified it.

25:18.316 --> 25:23.122
In other words, God committed himself on pain of death to fulfill his promise.

25:25.085 --> 25:31.675
There are other covenants that God made with Abraham's descendants, but each of them flows out of and is connected to this one.

25:32.816 --> 25:36.021
It's what theologians often speak of when they talk about the old covenant.

25:36.802 --> 25:42.610
The problem with the old covenant is that Abraham's children never did a good job at keeping their end of the bargain.

25:43.458 --> 25:51.346
They repeatedly demonstrated their disobedience and their lack of trust in God, the lack of trust that is on full display here at Kedish Barnia.

25:54.109 --> 25:55.670
So let me jump towards the New Testament.

25:56.751 --> 25:59.614
Because once again, you find this kind of covenant language.

26:00.655 --> 26:02.977
The occasion is a Passover meal.

26:04.239 --> 26:11.826
That's the remembrance, the reenactment of that night that Israel was saved from death by the blood sacrifice of a lamb.

26:13.186 --> 26:14.808
And this is not just any Passover.

26:15.008 --> 26:19.774
It's the last supper that Jesus shares with his disciples prior to his crucifixion.

26:20.495 --> 26:22.617
Now, they didn't know that's what was coming.

26:23.158 --> 26:23.778
Jesus did.

26:23.839 --> 26:28.724
And as part of that highly symbolic meal, Jesus takes some of the elements.

26:28.744 --> 26:32.729
He takes the bread, he takes the cup, and he pronounces new meaning over them.

26:33.670 --> 26:35.572
Here's what he says about the cup of wine.

26:36.894 --> 26:40.338
He took a cup, and when he had given things, he gave it to them, and they drank of it.

26:40.578 --> 26:46.308
And he said to them, this is my blood of the covenant, which is poured out for many.

26:48.251 --> 26:54.782
Now, if you go all the way back to the establishment of God's covenant with his people, it was a covenant that God sealed himself.

26:56.145 --> 26:59.110
God made himself the guarantee of the covenant.

27:00.692 --> 27:06.322
Now, Kedish Barnea, it was a covenant where the failure rested with the people, and yet it was God himself

27:06.786 --> 27:10.770
who had volunteered to pay the price if the covenant was broken.

27:13.353 --> 27:16.296
I talked about the two ways people without trust can respond.

27:17.057 --> 27:20.321
One is through irreligion, to reject God.

27:22.423 --> 27:32.594
If you think about that table, the night that Jesus broke bread and gave that cup, seated at that table was one such man, Judas.

27:33.794 --> 27:34.935
Judas had been with Jesus.

27:35.076 --> 27:36.858
He had seen the things that Jesus had done.

27:36.898 --> 27:38.660
He'd heard the things that Jesus had taught.

27:39.801 --> 27:44.987
And yet somewhere in that journey, Judas wasn't getting what he wanted.

27:46.710 --> 27:49.533
Or maybe he was just afraid of the enemies that he saw in the land.

27:50.794 --> 27:57.002
Because he could see that the most powerful religious and political leaders of his people were against Jesus.

27:57.783 --> 28:01.287
And that was probably not gonna end well for Jesus or the ones following him.

28:02.168 --> 28:03.730
Somewhere in that process,

28:04.194 --> 28:06.577
Judas decided, I'm out of here.

28:07.918 --> 28:11.262
And not just out of here, I'm gonna become the betrayer.

28:12.243 --> 28:16.607
And so Judas turned away, worse than turning away he turned against.

28:18.690 --> 28:26.318
The other thing I suggested is religion, committing yourself to some spiritual system that's gonna try to obligate God to accept you.

28:27.759 --> 28:30.322
There was another man who came to Jesus, not that night,

28:30.434 --> 28:31.275
of that last supper.

28:31.315 --> 28:34.438
But earlier, another man who came to Jesus is a man named Nicodemus.

28:35.439 --> 28:38.882
And Nicodemus was an extremely religious man.

28:38.942 --> 28:42.726
He was the religious of the religious by his status.

28:43.547 --> 28:45.028
And he was curious about Jesus.

28:45.089 --> 28:47.411
He could see that God's favor was on Jesus.

28:47.471 --> 28:48.952
He could see the miracles he did.

28:48.972 --> 28:51.795
He acknowledged Jesus as a great teacher.

28:53.217 --> 28:58.642
And obviously, a devout man like Nicodemus would want a great teacher like Jesus to teach him

28:58.850 --> 29:03.696
some new technique or some new knowledge or a better rule for life.

29:05.538 --> 29:11.345
But before Nicodemus can even form his question, Jesus cuts him off with a stunning statement.

29:11.385 --> 29:20.576
He says this, Jesus answered him, truly, truly, I say to you, unless one is born again, he cannot see the kingdom of God.

29:22.879 --> 29:25.522
And Nicodemus immediately sees the problem in this statement.

29:27.138 --> 29:32.366
Because Jesus is just told him that what he needs is something that he can't do for himself.

29:33.808 --> 29:35.510
He can't make himself be born.

29:35.710 --> 29:37.653
How many of you took responsibility for your birth?

29:39.656 --> 29:39.977
Nobody.

29:41.018 --> 29:44.904
Jesus just said what you need to be right with God is something you cannot do for yourself.

29:44.964 --> 29:47.067
You must be born again.

29:47.127 --> 29:54.738
Israel there at Kiddish Barnia revealed this deep heart problem, their absolute inability to trust God.

29:56.066 --> 29:59.293
They were not up to the task in their own strength to enter that promised land.

30:01.057 --> 30:09.416
It took a whole new generation since there had to be a born again people to enter into that land.

30:12.022 --> 30:15.730
In essence, Jesus says to Nicodemus, I know what you're about to ask me.

30:16.738 --> 30:21.625
You're going to ask me what you can do in your own strength to gain eternal life.

30:21.745 --> 30:24.709
What can you do to obligate God to let you into his heaven?

30:24.729 --> 30:28.815
And so let me just stop you right there and tell you that you can't do it.

30:29.997 --> 30:32.801
Your religiosity is never going to win the day.

30:32.841 --> 30:37.888
The old way of trying to please God and earn his favor needs to die.

30:39.230 --> 30:40.492
Jesus says there's a new way.

30:40.532 --> 30:41.874
There's a new life.

30:42.274 --> 30:47.361
A new generation, a regeneration that must happen, you must be born again.

30:47.402 --> 30:53.450
Do you see what Jesus has done for us on the cross?

30:55.614 --> 30:58.658
He's paid the blood price of the old covenant.

31:00.781 --> 31:03.024
The terms of the old covenant were not kept.

31:04.527 --> 31:05.668
It wasn't God's fault.

31:06.750 --> 31:08.112
He's not the one that messed up.

31:09.013 --> 31:09.554
We were.

31:10.786 --> 31:13.409
Israel was, Israel didn't uphold their end of the bargain.

31:15.111 --> 31:17.234
We haven't upheld our end of the bargain with God either.

31:18.816 --> 31:24.864
Now, maybe some of us think we've done a little better job than others, but I guarantee none of us have got a clean slate.

31:26.666 --> 31:39.282
And yet God, knowing from the outset that we would never be able to do our part, committed himself to do for us what we could not do for ourselves.

31:40.322 --> 31:41.343
Here's how Peter said it.

31:43.045 --> 31:55.678
He, speaking of Jesus, he himself bore our sins in his body on the tree that we might die to sin and live to righteousness by his wounds you have been healed.

31:57.640 --> 32:03.365
We see the cross wasn't just about bringing a close to the old covenant, it was the inauguration of a new covenant.

32:04.947 --> 32:07.890
Those who followed Jesus are people of a new generation.

32:08.738 --> 32:13.405
generation not birthed by human procreation by work of God's Holy Spirit.

32:14.746 --> 32:24.500
And as members of that new generation, we're invited by God into new life, a promise land, if you will, of hope and forgiveness in life.

32:28.085 --> 32:37.298
And I think every one of us at some point either has or is or will be standing

32:37.634 --> 32:39.337
at our own Kedish Barnia.

32:41.079 --> 32:45.586
God brings us to a place where the challenges before us are greater than our resources.

32:46.968 --> 32:53.779
And the question his spirit poses to us as it was to them is, will you trust me?

32:55.581 --> 32:58.366
Even though you don't see how this can be done, will you trust me?

33:01.891 --> 33:06.418
Maybe in your own journey, you've been pushing God away.

33:08.642 --> 33:11.106
like that generation who ended up wandering in the wilderness.

33:12.769 --> 33:15.092
Maybe your heart's been wandering away from God for a long time.

33:16.675 --> 33:20.020
Maybe not just wandering away, maybe you've slammed the door and dropped the bar in place.

33:21.923 --> 33:27.051
Maybe something happened in the past and you concluded that God could not be trusted.

33:28.674 --> 33:32.741
He must hate you to let something like that happen.

33:34.784 --> 33:36.146
And you've hated him right back.

33:38.530 --> 33:42.395
I would ask you to consider the man on the cross.

33:44.638 --> 33:52.389
The same God who persisted for 40 years to bring his people back to Kedish Barnia is willing to bring you back as well.

33:54.051 --> 34:02.342
The man on the cross literally prayed words of love and forgiveness over the very people who hated him so much that they applauded his death.

34:05.567 --> 34:08.050
You have not hated God too much for him to forgive you.

34:09.730 --> 34:17.220
And don't worry if you can't find it in yourself to be the kind of person or have the kind of faith that you think a Christian should have.

34:18.362 --> 34:25.271
I have talked to people like that and say, yeah, that sounds good, but I don't think I could ever have that kind of faith, as though it, again, depends on us.

34:27.173 --> 34:27.674
You can't.

34:29.817 --> 34:30.858
I don't have enough faith.

34:32.841 --> 34:39.730
But what you can do is simply say to God, I want your gift in my life.

34:39.810 --> 34:41.533
I submit myself to you.

34:41.713 --> 34:44.217
I need you to regenerate my heart.

34:45.478 --> 34:48.984
Please help me today to trust you.

34:51.928 --> 34:54.752
Maybe God's asking you to do something really hard.

34:57.636 --> 34:58.257
You follow him?

34:59.499 --> 35:04.426
You've trusted him, but he's brought to a place where there is something in front of you that looks insurmountable.

35:05.268 --> 35:09.554
The land is full of giants with fortified skyscrapers that reach up to heaven.

35:11.298 --> 35:20.428
Maybe it's dealing with some kind of chronic illness or pain in your own life or maybe it's the challenge of caring for others.

35:21.469 --> 35:31.780
You're a young parent and this thought of raising these little ones and all of their needs and all their demands and a world as crazy as this, that just seems like more than you can handle.

35:33.242 --> 35:37.106
Or maybe it's an aging family member or a spouse

35:37.538 --> 35:39.740
And you don't see how you can keep going.

35:39.781 --> 35:43.304
You can keep meeting the challenges that that care is requiring of you.

35:46.368 --> 35:48.871
Maybe it's a painful relationship that you don't know how to manage.

35:50.573 --> 35:53.476
You keep trying to find the peace in it, but you can't find the peace.

35:55.038 --> 35:59.523
That you and that person just cannot seem to get on the same page and you think this is hopeless.

36:00.444 --> 36:05.970
There's no way that I can continue to face this, that I can find the courage to

36:06.082 --> 36:07.785
Seek a reconciliation here.

36:10.889 --> 36:12.452
Maybe it's an opportunity for ministry.

36:14.154 --> 36:17.740
But the hurdles to make that a reality seem beyond your reach.

36:19.963 --> 36:21.025
Welcome to my Mondays.

36:23.288 --> 36:24.731
You can look at the needs of a church.

36:24.751 --> 36:26.033
You can look at the needs of people.

36:26.053 --> 36:27.054
You know the needs of friends.

36:27.074 --> 36:30.319
And you can think, that is more than I can do.

36:30.339 --> 36:33.083
I don't know where to start.

36:33.324 --> 36:34.866
I don't know how to help.

36:38.178 --> 36:53.298
I'll tell you this, one of the problems that Israel had there at Kedish Barnium was they decided that they were going to look at the entire battle before them as one big thing and base all their decisions on that, which isn't what God had asked them to do.

36:54.920 --> 37:02.130
He had asked them to cross the river and face the first battle and to trust that he would be with them in that.

37:03.074 --> 37:04.456
And I think all of us do that, right?

37:04.496 --> 37:06.879
That sort of cataclysmic thinking, right?

37:06.960 --> 37:15.352
Man, these are the children of the Nephilim and they got fortified cities that reach to the sky and we can inflate things to the point that we lose all hope.

37:17.434 --> 37:24.565
Now, they still had big challenges, but the only thing they had to do today was make the decision to trust God to cross the river.

37:25.846 --> 37:31.154
And soon enough, he was going to ask them to do a very challenging thing, which was to march around the walls of Jericho.

37:32.258 --> 37:34.822
But that was gonna be a process one day at a time.

37:36.044 --> 37:43.255
And so I'd encourage you, whatever that thing is that is just overwhelming you, because you've looked at the whole picture and said, this is just too much.

37:44.677 --> 37:45.619
Okay, it's too much.

37:46.981 --> 37:48.283
What has God asked you to do today?

37:49.484 --> 37:52.089
And can you trust him for today?

37:53.771 --> 37:55.494
Don't even worry about this week, okay?

37:58.098 --> 37:59.760
You and I may or may not be here in a week.

38:00.061 --> 38:00.882
We don't know that.

38:02.114 --> 38:06.481
All God's asking is to trust him for what is right here today.

38:08.223 --> 38:09.025
Can you do that?

38:10.387 --> 38:11.809
Is he faithful enough?

38:15.294 --> 38:25.029
Deep in our hearts, we may be thinking that God couldn't really love me and expect me to face a trial like this.

38:26.551 --> 38:31.058
Maybe he'd be like to show him to Israel and you'd say, you go step farther, you'd say, God must hate me.

38:31.810 --> 38:35.936
He must be just sitting up there in heaven and just enjoying watching me squirm.

38:38.801 --> 38:43.929
Again, I would say, don't forget the man on the cross.

38:45.371 --> 38:48.136
God is not distant from our pain.

38:49.418 --> 38:51.501
He is not distant from our fear.

38:52.583 --> 38:56.609
He chose to come and to live among us and he chose to die for us.

38:58.532 --> 38:59.794
Scripture says he faced

39:00.450 --> 39:01.972
all the temptations that we face.

39:03.694 --> 39:06.117
He paid the price we could not pay for ourselves.

39:08.900 --> 39:15.909
God is not distant from our pain or fear, and you are not distant from His heart.

39:17.591 --> 39:18.031
Let's pray.

39:22.136 --> 39:27.122
Lord Jesus, you know what the Kedesh Barneas are in each of our lives.

39:29.858 --> 39:44.260
And Lord, I pray for my brothers and sisters this morning, the ones who are right now in a fight facing a challenge at a place where they feel like giving up hope because they don't see how there could ever be victory.

39:46.563 --> 39:59.282
Father, I pray that you will grant them the courage and the strength and the provision of your power to help them deal with today.

40:02.370 --> 40:10.639
Or may they see, may they know in their heart of hearts that they are loved by you.

40:12.401 --> 40:22.972
Lord Jesus, may we not forget you, the man on the cross who loved us so much that you gave your life for us.

40:25.815 --> 40:32.082
Lord, may we rest in that and grant us the courage

40:32.834 --> 40:44.491
and the faith to trust you and not turn back, not run away, but to move forward knowing that we're not going there alone.

40:44.551 --> 40:45.793
You are the one who's with us.

40:48.737 --> 40:50.760
We pray these things in the powerful name of Jesus.

40:51.681 --> 40:52.082
Amen.

